ure remains opaque. This study contributes to a deeper understanding of age(ing) by exploring its construction through the analysis of extraordinary cases. Focusing on life narratives of centenarians and children with progeria, Julia Velten analyzes the way in which these people experience age(ing) and shows how these experiences can contribute to our understanding of age. Situated at the intersection of aging studies and medical humanities, the study explores what extraordinary age(ing) can tell us about aging processes in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aAging Studies. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aBody. 4aCentenarians. 4aCultural Studies. 4aIllness Narratives. 4aLife Writing. 4aLiterature. 4aMedicine. 4aProgeria. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh  aAging Studies.  aAmerican Studies.  aBody.  aCentenarians.  aCultural Studies.  aIllness Narratives.  aLife Writing.  aLiterature.  aMedicine.  aProgeria.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2022z9783111025094oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z978311076851040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839462775?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839462775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document